@startuml DeleteReport

actor Admin
boundary "ReportPage" as View #lightblue
participant ":reportRoute" as Route #lightblue
control ":authMiddleware" as Auth #Orange
control "reportController" as Controller #lightblue
participant ":reportService" as Service #lightblue
entity "reportModel" as Model #lightblue
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB #yellow

Admin -> View: 1. Select a report and click "Delete" icon
activate Admin
activate View

View -> View: 2. Show confirmation dialog
activate View
deactivate View

opt Cancel Deletion
    View --> Admin: 2.1. Cancel deletion 
end

Admin -> View: 3. Click "Confirm" button

View -> Route: 4. DELETE /api/v1/report/{reportId}
activate Route

Route -> Auth: 5. authenticateUser(req, res, next)
activate Auth
ref over Admin, View, Route, Auth, Controller, Service, Model, MongoDB : 6. Middleware verifies access token & admin role

Auth --> Route: 7. authentication success
deactivate Auth
    Route -> Controller: 8. deleteReport(req, res)
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Service: 9. deleteReport(reportId)
    activate Service

    Service -> Model: 10. deleteReport(reportId)
    activate Model
    Model -> MongoDB: 11. Delete report by ID
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB --> Model: 12. Return result
    deactivate MongoDB
    Model --> Service: 13. Return success
    deactivate Model

    alt Report exists

        Service --> Controller: 13.1. Return success

        Controller --> Route: 13.1.1. Return message success

        Route --> View: 13.1.2. Refresh report list

        View --> Admin: 13.1.3. Show "Report deleted successfully"
    else Report not found
        Service --> Controller: 13.2. Return error
        deactivate Service

        Controller --> Route: 13.2.1. Return 404 Not Found
        deactivate Controller

        Route --> View: 13.2.2. Show error
        deactivate Route

        View --> Admin: 13.2.3. Display "Report not found or already deleted"
        deactivate View
        deactivate Admin
    end
@enduml
